flowRoot.flowPara: Botanists have described three distinct types of
Cannabis that are generally distinguishable by a number of characteristics, and which have been given the names Cannabis sativa, Cannabis indica, and Cannabis ruderalis.

Although distinct forms exist, many or possibly most cultivated varieties are in fact hybrids of two or more types. In fact, hybrids are sometimes desirable to plant breeders for exhibiting unique characteristics.
We report precise admixture proportions (proportion of ancestry derived from each Cannabis species) for every sample.
Our comprehensive curated database of Cannabis land-races and species provides a background This allows us to accurately place contemporary strains in the context of ancestral genetic variation.
